{%- comment -%}
  Central asset map for case study photos.

  Why this file exists
  ---------------------
  The case-studies-data.json file is fetched client-side, so its image
  values cannot use the Liquid `asset_url` filter directly. Instead, the
  JSON references theme-shipped photos with the prefix `asset:filename.jpg`,
  and this snippet emits a JavaScript map that resolves those references
  at render time.

  How to add a new case study photo
  ---------------------------------
  1. Drop the image into `assets/` with a `cs-` prefix:
     e.g. `assets/cs-tanishq-diwali-2026-1.jpg`
  2. Add one line below — keep the filename in both places identical:
       window.__csAssetMap['cs-tanishq-diwali-2026-1.jpg'] = {{ 'cs-tanishq-diwali-2026-1.jpg' | asset_url | json }};
  3. In `assets/case-studies-data.json` reference it as
     `"src": "asset:cs-tanishq-diwali-2026-1.jpg"`.
{%- endcomment -%}

<script>
